The paper deals with privacy in anonymous communication networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses formalizing privacy goals and identifying their building blocks, which involves the use of data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper discusses practical assumptions and options, which could fall under the category of cyber-physical systems (cs.CY) or social and information networks (cs.SI).
